Dialogs.Dialog: Manaka
▲主人公＊▲.
Hmm？ What's wrong？
I've come up with a really good idea. Can you hear me out？
What's wrong？ If I can do something...
...Isn't Enoshima near Shona？
What happened to Enoshima？
Why don't we go there on a date next time？
I see. Isn't it unusual that you thought about a new date spot, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
...Huh？ That's... Yes！ You're always thinking about them, so doing sometimes it's okay.
I see, you're right.
Yeah！ I think Enoshima is a wonderful place！ You can go on a day trip, the fish is delicious and, uh... Shonan！
Shonan, huh...
Yes, Shonan. I'm kidding...
Yes.
Are you hiding something about this？
No？ At Enoshima...
Really？ I'm really glad！
I should do some research about it, right？ About Enoshima！ Hehe, are you looking forward for it？
(So you really wanted to go there, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
Now then, I wonder where ▲高嶺＊＊▲ is...
Manaka
▲主人公＊▲.
There's something different about you today, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...？
Really？
Hmm, the way you're dressed up...
Well, you know, it's Shonan...
...Don't look at me too much.
(She looks so cute...)
Manaka
▲主人公＊▲.
Ah, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！ You're early.
Yeah, I wanted to arrive early.
Aren't you wearing something different today ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
That's because, you know, I wonder if you'll take some photos again... Meanie.
(She's so cute...)
Manaka
Hehe♪
Are you having fun, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yeah. There's no sound coming from the inverter control of the ＶＶＶＦ.
Vee... What？
This vehicle is a new 500-type, so it has a ＶＶＶＦ inverter. The engine is making a humming noise, right？
So that was it？
That's right. Hehe♪
Say... Do you like railways that much ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
That's not the case, but I've been researching about trains for today.
I see...
Manaka
Ah, a 10-type vehicle...
Huh？
The blue vehicle that was parked before.
Are you addicted to trains ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
That's not it, but I looked it up before, you know？ I remembered some things, and I got curious.
I see. So that's the 10-type... Are there more of them？
lot of active vehicles, the popular 300-type, 1000-type, 2000-type...
(And I'm addicted to you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
Finally, we've arrived to Enoshima...
Manaka
Hmm, the weather's good... The weather is so nice for our first time at Enoshima.
That's right... Huh？ Where is the true Enoshima？
It seems that you can see it from Katase-Enoshima station, but you can't see it from Enoshima station.
I see. Well, let's go to the sea...
From here, a 3-minute straight walk on this road. Shall we go？
As expected of you！ Let's go, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！
We arrived！
Manaka
Yup, and the weather is so good today...
It's a 3-minute walk from here, right？
Hehe, that's right. But I want to take our time, I'm sure there are things I still don't know.
That's right, let's do that.
Of course！
Manaka
Wow...
Oh, Enoshima！
It looks a lot closer than I imagined. From here, it almost looks like a picture of a postcard.
Yeah, it looks good...
Besides, it really looks like the Dragon God really lives here.
Dragon God？
Enoshima has been worshiped since before Prince Shotoku, and En no Gyōja and Tokimasa Hojo also came to visit.
En no―― I see, I understand！
Do you want to continue？
(I didn't know that...)
Hah～！ Today you can clearly see the island.
Manaka
Yeah, it's really beautiful...
It really is...
When we came for the first time, I didn't notice it because I was just reviewing what I had read in my head.
It's really a nice view...
Alright, let's go！
Manaka
Hey, are you hungry？
Actually, I've been feeling hungry for a while now...
Enoshima has a lot of delicious foods, right？ I wonder what we should try...
Ah, don't tell me--！
Yeah, I brought a bento with me.
I wanna eat it！
Aren't you overdoing it？ If you want to eat an Enoshima's specialty, you can´t eat from the bento.
I'll prepare another stomach from that specialty.
Geez... Well then, let's find a place where we can have our bento, okay？
Now then, where are we going...
Do you mind going to, ▲スポット名＊＊＊＊＊＊▲？
Manaka
Yeah, that sounds good as a first stop.
Thank you for the food！
Manaka
I'm glad you liked it. You ate a lot next time.
Your bento is always so good ▲高嶺＊＊▲！
Geez... Hey, why don't we go see Samuel Cooking Garden next？
Oh, doesn't that sound nice？ Let's go！
Well then, it's almost time...
Do you want to the ▲スポット名＊＊＊＊＊＊▲ next？
Manaka
Yeah, I wanna go.
Next, we have to go over there...
Wanna go visit ▲スポット名＊＊＊＊＊＊▲ next？
Manaka
Yes, agreed！
You mentioned Ryujin-sama before, but there are many depictions of dragons with many heads here, right？
Manaka
One of the Shrine's treasures is a scroll depicting Enoshima Engi. The Celestial Maiden and the dragon.
Is the Celestial Maiden disciplining the dragon？
Hehe, the correct answer is that the dragon that brings disaster falls in love with the Celestial Maiden.
The dragon repented and became a protector, forever united with the Celestial Maiden.
Over there！ If I'm with you, I won't need a guide, right ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
I don't think so... I just did some research before coming.
(What do you mean ▲高嶺＊＊▲...？)
Manaka
Oh, look... it's the crest of "three scales" again.
Is Mitsuuroko a guy with three triangles lined up？ Is that used in many places？
Probably because it is the family crest of the Hojo family, which is related to the island.
It's based on the scales of the three dragons that Tokimasa Hojo received when he visited the Dragon God.
Hojo Tokimasa, huh... Isn't that a story that appears in history textbooks ？
...Huh？
Didn't Tokimasa Hojo appear in a textbook？
Yes, it really comes in a history textbook.
Manaka
Hah... I need to stop doing that.
...What happened？
I've been looking into some things, because we've been coming so much... Maybe that's what makes a difference.
Why？
I get excited while walking and smelling nice things. However, I worry about the Goddess Benzaiten becoming mad.
Eh... isn't that a good thing to do？
But, if we can travel without checking anything, get lost or wander together, I'm sure it will be fun...
I'm having fun, okay？ Don't worry.
... Don't lie.
It's true, all these kinds of things remind me of you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
...Thank you.
...It's true.
What do you mean？
Hmm... I like you because you're so kind.
(I'm getting embarrassed.)
Manaka
From here there are lots of slopes and stairs... Don't you get tired of walking？
I can see that... I'm getting a little tired.
But, it's a good training, right？ Muscles you don't normally use are trained.
Hahaha...
Okay, raise your knees a little more and do your best▼
It's seems really busy over here.
Manaka
Hehe！ Climbing through this side, you'll find the first Enoshima Shrine.
And a lot of souvenirs shops and delicious things！
Yes, it has been a popular tourist destination since the Edo period, for people who visit Goddess Benzaiten.
I see... Is that the history behind it？
There was a bronze Torii Gate at the entrance, right？ That was also built in the 4th year of Bunsei.
Are you familiar with it？ Did you look it up？
Yes, I did a little research about it.
A little, huh... As expected of you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！
Manaka
This is Hetsumiya...
It's difficult to read... Of course, did you check it too？
Yes, a little.
Hetsumiya is one of the three main shrines in Enoshima. Also famous for enshrining Myon Benzaiten.
Another Benzaiten？
Yes, it's also called Naked Benzaiten. The legend says that if a couple comes, it separates them...
What！？
It's okay, this place blesses marriage. Do you see that？ There are a lot of pink votive tablets.
Oh, I see... Couple votives. It has written a lot of things. Well, what does it say？
No, don't！ Geez... it's bad to read them.
I'm sorry...
Samuel Cooking Garden. I see... it's a beautiful place. Is Samuel Cooking's house also there？
Manaka
That's not true. Originally, it was a botanical garden, but when it was renovated in 2002 from an Irish trader--
...What's wrong？
Hmm... Hey, why don't we climb the lighthouse？
Amazing...
Oh... it's quite the view. You can see it far away...
It really is, the sea and the city are beautiful... Besides, the sea breeze feels good.
I've noticed this wonderful place before.
I see... Are you glad we come here？
Yup...
Manaka
Isn't this lively somehow？ It feels like we're in a festival.
And whenever we come, it smells delicious, doesn't it？ Want to grab something to eat？
But, eating while walking...
...Can't we？
Hmm... Since we're in Enoshima, we can make an exception. Hehe！
Alright！ What should we do？
Then we should buy some sazae, roasted rice crakers, shirasu rice crackers, and then...
Wait... Is it okay to eat that much？
We can split it in half, that's why it's fine. Isn't that a nice plan？
Manaka
Benzaiten-sama has a pure white, beautiful face.
You're right.
Yes！ I've never seen such a beautiful Goddess.
...Isn't that something strange for you to say ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Say it's beautiful.
...Who？
Benzaiten-sama...
Perhaps you believe in the legend about Benzaiten's envy？
Not really... But, I'm still worried.
Manaka
Hey, we're climbing the lighthouse next, right？
That's right. Let's go！
It's very beautiful today...
You can see a panoramic view of Shohan...
Izu Peninsula, Hakone, Tanzawa Mountains. Is that Yougahama？ Inamuragasaki. Oh, the Boso Peninsula！
As expected, you did look into the scenery around.
Huh？ I did nothing special...
(Yes. You seem like someone who can do everything, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
Manaka
Ah, it's Ryugu.
It's written like dragon, and it's read like "wadatsumi".
Wadatsumi is an ancient word for the god of the sea. It has a charming little face, right？
Ah, do you want to be punished？
I'm sorry, Dragon God.
Say it more like... Teehee▼ okay？
Hmm...
I'm sorry, Dragon God. Teehee▼
...You're forgiven.
I see... There are quite a lot of stairs...
Manaka
Hehe, we're almost at Iwaya！
It's really cool, after all...
Hmm... Now it's a tourist facility, but--
When it was still a natural cave, it must have been a more strict place...
It used to be a place where people came to practice.
Yes. When Kobo Daishi visited, Benzaiten-sama appeared.
Maybe it's not gone after all...
Hah... We finally arrived.
Manaka
Look at those interesting rock formations.
Interesting？
Of course, different layers are formed due to the sea bed influence and the erosion of waves... Hehe♪
Yes, that sounds like fun... So far, we've gone down a lot of stairs.
Do you want to compete about who can climb back first？ Let's go！
(Sometimes I can't match your energy ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
Manaka
Ah, this area may be good to take photos, ▲主人公＊▲...
You're right, then let's take some.
Yes！
Manaka
Oh, this area feels like Enoshima.
Okay, let's take a picture.
Yup.
Manaka
Hey, why don't we take some photos for today's memories？
Yeah, sure.
Huh, what is this？
Manaka
What's wrong？
This feels so mysterious. Why？
I don't know, but the position of the sun and the refraction of the lens may cause some weird effects...
But, it's really nice...
Ah... Maybe it's the wonderful thing your mother told you about, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...
Ah！！ Well then, I'm sure we'll... We'll treasure this forever, right？
Yup...
Huh？
Manaka
Huh, what's wrong？
I think this may be...
It's amazing... A photo of Hagoromo...
Yes, it looks like the Celestial Maiden...
It can't be... But, that makes me happy.
This is a secret only both of us share.
Yup...
Now then... it's almost time for the sun to set.
Manaka
Hmm... We have to go back home soon.
What's wrong？
Hmm. There is something I'm curious about... Ah, it's over there.
What's that？
"Ryuren Bell of Love"...
"Ryuren Bell of Love"？
To end our day, can we stop by a little？
Alright, let's go.
Manaka
Hey... isn't the sunset beautiful today？
Yes, it really is.
I want to go there again before we go home... Okay？
Yes, I want to go too. Alright, let's go！
The sunset is amazing... Isn't that the Bell of Ryuren？
Manaka
That is the Bell of Promise, according to the legend, lovers will be tied forever when the bell is rang.
And look over there. Lots of keys.
That's true.
Manaka
Do you remember？ We went there together...
Yes... It's Cape Aijo. Maybe it's because we're in Enoshima？
Hmm, it might be that...
Manaka
I wanted to come to Enoshima because Mama told me.
Your mother did, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Enoshima is the place where Papa and Mama dated back when they were students.
She said to me, "Manaka, you should look into it, you're a little blunt, so dress up cutely and go".
That kind of thing to say to you――
Because, even though we came all this way today, we're just studying history...
That's also a good point of yours, isn't it ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Thank you... Yeah, this is enough.
Huh？
Mama said that maybe something really strange and wonderful would happen in Enoshima...
Something strange and wonderful...
She didn't tell me what it was... But, I think that's okay.
Two people who met in this wide world walked in a place they didn't know, and felt each other's feelings...
That's not strange nor wonderful... Or so I thought.
That is why, I want to ring the bell with you.
Yes...
Hey...
The Dragon and the Celestial Maiden were happily tied together... I'm kidding.
The sunset is amazing... Is that the Bell of Ryuren？
Manaka
That is the Bell of Promise, according to the legend, lovers will be tied forever when the bell is rang.
And look over there. There are lot of keys.
Ah, truly.
All those keys are from the lovers' sad feelings.
Manaka
Hey, do you remember it？ We we're here before...
Yes... It's Cape Aijo. Maybe it's because we're in Enoshima？
Hmm, that might be it...
Manaka
The other day, Mama told me something.
Enoshima is the place where Papa and Mama dated when they were students.
I see. Is it that good of a place？
Yes, and then...
Mama thought a mysterious and strange thing would occur, so she would be with him someday...
A mysterious and wonderful thing？
Yes, however, she couldn't just tell me what it was...
When we came here together, I thought maybe I might understand.
I see....
But, it's okay. Because...
Today, we came here together; and I love you after all...
And I thought I wanted to walk with you, forever.
So, I want to ring the bell with you.
Yes...
I love you...
The Dragon and the Celestial Maiden are always together, right？
Yeah, forever...
The sunset is amazing... Is that the Bell of Ryuren？
Manaka
That is the Bell of Promise, according to the legend, lovers will be tied forever when the bell is rang.
And look over there. Lots of keys.
Ah, it's true.
Manaka
Geez, don't you remember it？ Before, in Atami――
Yes... That's Cape Aijo. Maybe it's because we're in Enoshima？
Hmm, I think that was it...
Manaka
You know... Mama told me something.
You mom？ What did she say, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
She said "Manaka, you're a little tomboyish, so I'm worried. Do your best to look cute in front of him".
Your mother said that！.. But why Enoshima？
Enoshima is the place where Papa and Mama used to date when they were students. So, I asked him in secret...
A very strange and wonderful thing happened, and my always serious Papa kissed Mama for the first time...
So that was it... But what's so strange and wonderful？
He didn't tell me.
But I wonder if Enoshima has some secret that makes girls more attractive than usual, so...
A secret... Is it something like that？
I love you...
I love you too.
Hey, why don't we ring the bell too？
Of course！
It seems a little different from what I imagined.
Surprisingly, it's kind of a bitter sound, right？
Yes. But it's always the same. Like the Dragon and the Celestial Maiden.
That's right.
Manaka
Hehe, hey, I want to ring the bell again.
Let's ring it then.
Maybe I've gotten a little used to the sound, from the first time we've heard it.
You're right, me too.
It was fun today as well. The sunset is also very beautiful...
Did your mother also see the sunset before going back home, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes, I'm sure. Even thought Papa puts a bothered face, I'm sure it was very romantic.
I'm sure it was...
I'm sure they always saw the sunset, and then...
And then？
You know what... Meanie.
See, you knew...
Yes...
Let's come again, okay？
Manaka
It was really fun... But, it's almost time to go back home today. Can we come again？
Yes. When you get home, will you show the photos to your mom？
Yes... But I'm sure Mama still won't tell me.
I think it's a memory for them too. I'm sure they'd like it to remain a secret...
I'm sure...
Oh！ I found a good one！ Wait a minute！
Hmm？
Look at this strap！
Maybe it's the Celestial Maiden？
Yes, it's an Enoden！ So cute～▼
That...
Ah, it seems like our transport is here. Let's go！
(It seems this will be a good memory too, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
Manaka
Hah... We arrived at the station.
Are you reluctant to go？
Yes. I know we will come again, so I wonder why I feel like this...
Ah, the train has arrived. Shall we go？
Yes...
Ah look, it's a 20-type！ Let's go inside quickly.
(I'm getting jealous of the Enoden...)
